subproject.description:
1- Employment creation for migrant youth is mainstreamed into national development framework.
2- Policies and measures are implemented to help young returnees enter and remain in the labour market.
3- Innovative interventions to create concrete employment and training opportunities for the youth developed and implemented in 3 states (States level).
4- Enhancing capacity of MF providers and clients to adopt best practice MF services and to advocate for enabling MF Policy and regulatory environment.
5- Youth employment is mainstreamed into the national development framework
donor_long: UNDP AS AA FOR JP PASS THROUGH
subproject.title: Youth Employment Opportunities

subproject.corporate outcome: Capacities of national and local institutions enhanced to scale up proven MDG acceleration interventions and to plan, monitor, report and evaluate the MDG progress in the context of related national development priorities
